Closes the last optional item from the v1.3.0 post-release backlog by
adding the long-deferred dashboard smoke-test infrastructure.

Adds vitest + jsdom + @testing-library/react + msw to the dashboard
workspace as devDeps, plus a four-file scaffold:

  src/test/setup.ts        — jsdom shims (EventSource / matchMedia /
                              ResizeObserver / IntersectionObserver) +
                              MSW lifecycle (listen / resetHandlers /
                              close) + jest-dom matchers.
  src/test/msw-server.ts   — node-mode setupServer.
  src/test/msw-handlers.ts — defaults for /api/alerts/* (matches the
                              Phase 8 channel shape exactly), /api/slo/*,
                              /api/governance/scheduler/*, plus a
                              permissive /api/* catch-all that returns
                              {} or [] based on a path heuristic so
                              smoke tests stay green for pages that
                              fan out to many endpoints.
  src/test/render.tsx      — renderPage(<Page/>) wrapper that injects
                              QueryClientProvider + wouter Router; one
                              fresh QueryClient per render, retry off,
                              refetch-on-focus off.

Three smoke tests scaffolded:

  pages/__tests__/not-found.test.tsx     — canary (no hooks).
  pages/__tests__/alert-center.test.tsx  — exercises Phase 8 + 9 push +
                                            6 query keys.
  pages/__tests__/alerts.test.tsx        — exercises raw EventSource +
                                            useMutation + 3 useQuery.

Bug surfaced + fixed: the AlertCenter NotificationChannels component
called `ch.failureRate.toFixed(1)` without defending against missing
fields. The Phase 8 shape always includes failureRate, but mock
fallback shapes did not — fixed to coerce missing numerics to 0.

tsconfig.json excludes test files + scaffolding so production builds
remain unchanged.

